Package: libzkp-hamiltonian1
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Zero-Knowledge Proof library based on Hamiltonian Cycle
 A cryptographic library implementing Zero-Knowledge Proof (ZKP) based on
 the Hamiltonian Cycle problem (Blum 1986) with NIZK (Non-Interactive
 Zero-Knowledge) transformation via Fiat-Shamir heuristic.
 .
 This allows a Prover to convince a Verifier that they know a Hamiltonian
 cycle in a graph without revealing the cycle itself.
 .
 This package contains the shared library.

Package: libzkp-hamiltonian-dev
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Section: libdevel
Depends: libzkp-hamiltonian1 (= ${binary:Version}),
         libssl-dev,
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: Zero-Knowledge Proof library - development files
 A cryptographic library implementing Zero-Knowledge Proof (ZKP) based on
 the Hamiltonian Cycle problem (Blum 1986) with NIZK transformation.
 .
 This package contains the development headers and static library.

Package: zkp-hamiltonian-tools
Architecture: any
Depends: libzkp-hamiltonian1 (= ${binary:Version}),
         ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: Zero-Knowledge Proof CLI tools
 Command-line utilities for ZKP Hamiltonian operations:
 .
  - zkp-keygen: Generate key pair (public graph + secret cycle)
  - zkp-prover: Generate NIZK proof from graph and secret
  - zkp-verifier: Verify proof against public graph
 .
 These tools are used for authentication between SecuBox nodes.
